ABUJA – Some invited guests and supporters to the Rochas Okorocha’s 2023 presidential declaration, on Monday expressed anger as they were locked out of the International Conference Centre (ICC) hall, where the declaration took place. Despite having tags and invitation cards to prove that they were invited for the occasion, they were still stopped by the security men at the gate. Even Journalists and staff of the Rochas Foundation were not spared the humiliation, they were also denied entry to the programme that lasted less than an our. Okorocha Declares For Presidency, Pledges To Surpass Buhari In… Delta: Keston Okoro Dumps PDP For APC Some of these invited guests and supporters were seen complaining of how they were treated at the occasion. It was also gathered that several supporters and professionals who were at the ICC for professional jobs have expressed displeasure over the incident.